# 2025-03-01 (cont. 0 — project inception)

Established project scope and reference material. No code yet.

## What Was Built

* CLAUDE.md — project-level instructions combining base dev standards with 8088 emulator context.
* docs/Intel_8086_Family_Users_Manual.pdf — downloaded the October 1979 Intel MCS-86 Family User's Manual (the primary reference for this project).
* .plan and memory directory structure initialized.

## Key Design Choices

* Validation target: SingleStepTests/8088 hardware-generated test suite (https://github.com/SingleStepTests/8088).
  - JSON v2 format: 10,000 tests per opcode, each with initial CPU state, final (changed-only) state, and per-cycle bus activity.
  - Test environment: 1MB writable RAM, no wait states, address wraps at 0xFFFFF.
  - Half of tests execute from prefetched queue; queue fetches beyond initial contents return NOP (0x90).
* First tests will target the CPU state object — it's the foundational data structure the test suite provides and validates.

? Register overlap modeling (AX = AH:AL etc.) — needs spec reading before deciding.
? Flags representation — individual flags vs raw 16-bit value vs both.
? Memory model — part of CPU state or separate collaborator.
? .NET version and project structure not yet decided.
? Cycle-level accuracy vs instruction-level accuracy as initial target.

